ormel, Cornwall, England":"Restormel, Cornwall, England","Cardinham, Cornwall, England":"Cardinham, Cornwall, England","Chilton Cantelo, Somerset, England":"Chilton Cantelo, Somerset, England","United Kingdom":"United Kingdom","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Bodmin, Cornwall, England":"Bodmin, Cornwall, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Cardinham II was born in 1145, in Bodmin, Cornwall, England, his father, Robert FitzWilliam de Cardinham, was 30 and his mother, Annora \"Agnes\" de Mandeville, was 25. He married Matilda Fitz Roger in 1172, in Chilton Cantelo, Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1186, in Restormel, Cornwall, England, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1145–1186":"1145–1186","1155–1234":"1155–1234","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1172–1252":"1172–1252","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1115–1177":"1115–1177","1120–1169":"1120–1169","1115":"1115","1169":"1169","1234":"1234","1145":"1145","1177":"1177","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1120":"1120","1252":"1252","1172":"1172","after 1169":"pärast 1169","Restormel, Cornwall, England":"Restormel, Cornwall, England","Cardinham, Cornwall, England":"Cardinham, Cornwall, England","Chilton Cantelo, Somerset, England":"Chilton Cantelo, Somerset, England","United Kingdom":"United Kingdom","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Bodmin, Cornwall, England":"Bodmin, Cornwall, England"},"fi":{"1145–1186":"1145–1186","1155–1234":"1155–1234","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1172–1252":"1172–1252","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","1115–1177":"1115–1177","1120–1169":"1120–1169","1115":"1115","1169":"1169","1234":"1234","1145":"1145","1177":"1177","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1120":"1120","1252":"1252","1172":"1172","after 1169":"1169 jälkeen","Restormel, Cornwall, England":"Restormel, Cornwall, England","Cardinham, Cornwall, England":"Cardinham, Cornwall, England","Chilton Cantelo, Somerset, England":"Chilton Cantelo, Somerset, England","United Kingdom":"Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Bodmin, Cornwall, England":"Bodmin, Cornwall, England"},"fr":{"1145–1186":"1145–1186","1155–1234":"1155–1234","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1172–1252":"1172–1252","1175–Female":"1175–Décédée","1115–1177":"1115–1177","112